name: TimeZone

unions.name: Error
unions.comment: Represents an error that may occur when trying to get the local zone.

values.name: getZone
values.comment:
Try to get the local time zone. If the task succeeds, then you get the zone
name along with the `Time.Zone`.

values.name: version
values.comment: What release of the IANA Time Zone Database is this data from?

values.name: zones
values.comment:
You can look up an unevaluated zone by its zone name in the `zones` dictionary.

    import Dict
    import TimeZone exposing (zones, america__new_york)


    Dict.get "America/New_York" zones

    -- Just america__new_york
